data.text: @_MarkL33 Fine. Upper arm a bit sore but thats probably more from being stabbed with a needle in arm
@AndrewYee2 How you feeling now? Any side effects?
@_MarkL33 When I got to right place, its big room with seats for about 30 people to wait for vaccine. And then about 30 seats for people to wait the 15 minutes

@_MarkL33 No. I was there 30 minutes and that includes 15 minutes waiting till after vaccine (in case have any side effects). Would have been shorter if I went to correct floor. The queue if booked via GP looked bit busier.
@AndrewYee2 Was there a long queue at the actual place?
@_MarkL33 When I went on NHS to book, I did end up in a Ticketmaster type online queue. It said something like I was number 500 in queue and wait about 5 minutes. Ended up waiting about 40 seconds

@_MarkL33 Who knows what it will be for you and all the other younger than 40 people. They may continue offering to different ages. Or maybe open up to everyone but the NHS app would Probably be busier than Ticketmaster when Adele tickets go on sale.
@_MarkL33 No letter or text. I assume at some point in future if I had not bothered to book myself, I would have got letter or text
@AndrewYee2 Ah ok. Thanks. So they didn't send you a letter or text? Thought they would.

@_MarkL33 But I believe generally you get a text and then letter few days after. After they have offered to all 40+ and most had it, maybe it will be open for everyone else to book appointment themselves (or just wait for the text/letter)
@_MarkL33 They didn't. I just went on NHS web site when I heard in news they were now offering vaccine to 42+
@AndrewYee2 How did they contact you to get the vaccine? Text or post?
